Renée Adorée https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ren%C3%A9e_Ador%C3%A9e 0 Renée Adorée or Jeanne de la Fonte (30 September 1898 – 5 October 1933) was a French actress who appeared in Hollywood silent movies during the 1920s. She is most famous for her role as Melisande in the melodramatic romance and war epic The Big Parade.
